               <p>JOHN GLANSFIELD. I live at Weldhill, Herts. On the 27th of December my father's stable was broken open, and the bridle taken away. I locked it at ten o'clock at night, and found it broken open at six the next morning. I saw the bridle again at Bow-street, where the prisoner was taken. He lived about a mile from me.</p>
               <p>
            
                  <persName id="t18180114-154-person1087">
                  JOHN 
                  UPTON
               <interp inst="t18180114-154-person1087" type="surname" value="UPTON"></interp>
                     <interp inst="t18180114-154-person1087" type="given" value="JOHN"></interp>
                     <interp inst="t18180114-154-person1087" type="gender" value="male"></interp>
                  </persName>
            . I am a patrol. On the 27th of December, about half-past nine o'clock in the morning, I stopped the prisoner in Goswell-street - road, with the bridle on his shoulder, and twelve dead fowls, quite warm.</p>
               <p>(Property produced and sworn to.)</p>
               <p>Prisoner's Defence. I bought them.</p>
               <p>
                  <rs id="t18180114-154-verdict828" type="verdictDescription">
                     <interp inst="t18180114-154-verdict828" type="verdictCategory" value="guilty"></interp>
               GUILTY
            </rs>. Aged 30.</p>
               <p>
                  <rs id="t18180114-154-punish829" type="punishmentDescription">
